ule out the Arnett $^{56}$Ni decay model\nfor SN\\,2020qlb's light curve due to unphysical parameter results. Our most\nfavored power source is the magnetic dipole spin-down energy deposition of a\nmagnetar. Two to three near peak oscillations, intriguingly similar to those of\nSN\\,2015bn, were found in the magnetar model residuals with a timescale of\n$32\\pm6$ days and an amplitude of 6$\\%$ of peak luminosity. We rule out\ncentrally located undulation sources due to timescale considerations; and we\nfavor the result of ejecta interactions with circumstellar material (CSM)\ndensity fluctuations as the source of the undulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 May 2022 09:10:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Dec 2022 20:03:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-01"}
