raction of Mg II correlates tightly with that of Lyman-alpha\n(LyA), which we interpret as an indication that the escape fraction of both\nspecies is controlled by resonant scattering in the same low column density\ngas. Furthermore, we show that the combination of the Mg II emission and dust\nattenuation can be used to estimate the escape fraction of LyC statistically.\nThese findings confirm that Mg II emission can be adopted to estimate the\nescape fraction of LyA and LyC in local star-forming galaxies and may serve as\na useful indirect indicator at the Epoch of Reionization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 May 2022 14:01:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-20"}
